Subject: Re: [T2] 1969 Westy cots

> Hi.... I just bought a 1968 westy and found two cots inside. One for over the 
> front seats and one  installed on the roof. What are the official names for 
> these cots ?
 
From the 68 Westy owners manual, page 2: 
The one over the front seats is called ''Children's hammock''. (#9)
The one up top is called ''Bed". (#22) 
http://www.geocities.com/thegreatjose/VW/68westypage2.JPG

Page 8 tells you how to use and store the hammock:
http://www.geocities.com/thegreatjose/VW/68westypage8.JPG

They changed the name of the bed to cot on page 15!!:
http://www.geocities.com/thegreatjose/VW/68westypage15.JPG

The complete 68 manual is here:
http://www.geocities.com/thegreatjose/VW/68WestyManual.html
